{
  "texts": [
    "However, the causal attention mask precludes this: any row in the residual stream corresponding to position i must be invariant to changes in rows corresponding to positions j > i.",
    "This interpretation is supported by Theorem 2, which we turn to next.",
    "A proof of Theorem 1 is provided in Section C. We note that this theorem does not depend on the order in which P and Y P are given as input: the same impossibility result holds for reversed inputs [Y P; P].",
    "2.2The possibility of inverse permutation learning with an unrestricted attention mask.Our next result serves to reinforce the key intuition from the prior section; namely, that the causal attention mask precludes the transfer of information which is necessary to perform inverse permutation learning.",
